One Vanderbilt: One Vanderbilt Ave. (51 E 42nd St.)
Commentary
Servicer Watch List

WatchList Commentary As of: 09/2022

Updated Commentary

The loan is subserviced by JLL. Collateral is a 274-unit independent and assisted living seniors facility built in 1991 and located in West Chester, PA. The property is improved with three 3-story buildings. 9/1/2022 - The loan is on the watchlist due to low occupancy, floating rate loan occupancy below 90% of UW and due to a Floater DSCR that is less than 1.00x and less than 90% of NOI "in place" as of U/W (Uses normalized FYEBA DSCR). Q1 2022 occupancy was 52.50% and -0.12x DSCR. YE 2021 occupancy was 21.68% and 0.13x DSCR. Per sub 8/1/2022 WL comment, This community is in phase one of a three phased, $6MM+ renovation of the IL common spaces which is scheduled to be completed in early 2023. The renovation will add new dining venues, refresh the corridors and update and consolidate the salon, spa and fitness/wellness into one area. Additionally, the community has 11 units under renovation with upgraded finishes that will be completed in Q4. Watermark has stabilized the leadership team and recently hired a new sales director. When phase one of the renovation is completed in September (which will include several of the dining venues), we believe this will improve marketability even though there will be an additional 6 months of construction.
